TECHNOTE (FAQ)
QUESTION: How do I enable processing of encrypted data objects?
ANSWER: After collecting a batch of data, the auditing log might indicate "missed - cannot decipher encrypted data object". This comes with an encrypted data object notification in the comprehensive section. To fix this issue, ensure no tasks are currently running in the system. Use SSH to log in to your Data Server(s) and input the below command at the prompt;

psql -U dfuser dfdata -c "insert into adminknobs (name,value,description,valuetype,use) VALUES ('decrypt_files','1','Decipher encrypted data objects','int','1')"

You should receive the following response; 
INSERT 0 1
If so, input the next command and wait for the UI to reload;
service siqinit restart

You should now be able to run normal collections and encrypted data objects will be processed. However, if you're using a policy that keeps the original files preserved and only shows an encrypted file view that when accessed, fetches the original file, you may encounter storage issues. This is because the Data Server will attempt to decrypt every encrypted file, which could lead to a significant increase in the disk space occupancy.
